'''''Rody and Mastico''''' is a 1989 educational [[interactive storybook]] video game for children, released on [[Atari ST]], [[Amiga]], [[Amstrad CPC]] and [[DOS]]. The game was available in English, French, and German. The game was coded by Jean-Michel Forgeas. A seventh unofficial episode, Rody in Ibiza, was developed by fans in 2016.<ref>''[https://lacrearthur.github.io/RodyAIbiza/#/ Rody A Ibiza]'': github link of the unofficial suite.</ref>

== Plot and gameplay ==
The game consists of 6 parts, each developing the story further toward its ultimate conclusion. The protagonist Rody and his companion Mastico are on a quest to locate the multicoloured star. To progress through the story, players must correctly answer questions.

